WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Do you want subtitles for any video?
-=[ ai.OpenSubtitles.com ]=-

2
00:02:15.510 --> 00:02:17.179
Keep going!

3
00:02:17.262 --> 00:02:19.139
Bring it on down!

4
00:02:19.222 --> 00:02:20.474
-That's it!
-Come on!

5
00:02:20.557 --> 00:02:21.975
-Keep moving!
-Back into it.

6
00:02:24.728 --> 00:02:26.103
Three more in here.

7
00:02:28.815 --> 00:02:30.692
Three more in there.

8
00:02:31.818 --> 00:02:32.819
You. go with them!

9
00:02:33.987 --> 00:02:35.405
Two more in here.

10
00:02:39.701 --> 00:02:40.994
Two more in here.

11
00:02:48.585 --> 00:02:50.587
You three. in this one.

12
00:02:52.422 --> 00:02:53.715
Oh. please. please.

13
00:02:54.925 --> 00:02:57.010
Our home. it's already crowded.

14
00:02:57.094 --> 00:02:59.721
There's 15.000 of us.

15
00:02:59.805 --> 00:03:01.139
Be glad you only got three.

16
00:03:04.309 --> 00:03:06.978
-Maybe crowded ain't so bad.
-Mind yourself.

17
00:03:08.230 --> 00:03:10.899
You don't like it.
go and carp to Lord Ormund.

18
00:03:10.982 --> 00:03:12.317
See what good it does you.

19
00:03:25.372 --> 00:03:29.459
It is only regarding
the lodging situation. my lord.

20
00:03:29.543 --> 00:03:32.087
You are unhappy with
your lodgings. Lord Footly?

21
00:03:32.170 --> 00:03:34.423
It is only that we are very fond
of our ancestral home.

22
00:03:34.506 --> 00:03:36.341
You are sleeping in our bedchamber.

23
00:03:37.300 --> 00:03:39.636
You bent the knee to the pretender.
Rhaenyra Targaryen.

24
00:03:39.720 --> 00:03:41.638
did you not. Lady Footly?

25
00:03:41.722 --> 00:03:42.723
We did.

26
00:03:43.515 --> 00:03:46.810
Then mayhaps I should remind you
that the wage of treason is death.

27
00:03:46.893 --> 00:03:48.353
We do not seek conflict. my lord.

28
00:03:49.062 --> 00:03:50.731
Tumbleton has no battlements.

29
00:03:50.814 --> 00:03:52.524
Our people know only trade.

30
00:03:52.607 --> 00:03:55.317
We never thought to see war.

31
00:03:55.402 --> 00:03:57.279
So you swore to her out of fear.

32
00:03:57.362 --> 00:03:59.948
We swore because she is the queen.

33
00:04:03.243 --> 00:04:04.745
Is she?

34
00:04:14.963 --> 00:04:17.132
Or is she a bitch with a dragon?

35
00:04:21.428 --> 00:04:24.973
My purpose is to restore the rightful line
to the Iron Throne.

36
00:04:26.057 --> 00:04:28.560
It follows from that
that I must be well rested.

37
00:04:30.020 --> 00:04:34.316
It follows from that that I must have
acceptable lodgings.

38
00:04:35.317 --> 00:04:38.570
I will ensure that my men
remain on their best behavior

39
00:04:38.653 --> 00:04:40.238
whilst in your town.

40
00:04:42.282 --> 00:04:43.700
Provided. of course...

41
00:04:46.661 --> 00:04:48.830
that you remain on yours.

42
00:04:48.914 --> 00:04:50.248
See them out.

43
00:04:52.834 --> 00:04:54.169
Don't.

44
00:04:54.795 --> 00:04:58.256
When dealing with those beneath you.
you must be fair. but firm.

45
00:04:58.340 --> 00:04:59.758
Yes. sire.

46
00:05:02.844 --> 00:05:04.012
My prince.

47
00:05:04.095 --> 00:05:06.348
My lord. a raven from Storm's End

48
00:05:06.431 --> 00:05:09.142
carrying more excuses
from Lord Borros Baratheon.

49
00:05:16.399 --> 00:05:18.944
That lackwit sealed a marriage pact
between Prince Aemond

50
00:05:19.027 --> 00:05:21.947
and one of his horse-faced daughters.

51
00:05:22.030 --> 00:05:23.907
And yet. where is he now?

52
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:26.034
Send another raven that he can understand.

53
00:05:26.117 --> 00:05:28.578
This one mayhaps with drawings
rather than letters.

54
00:05:34.376 --> 00:05:36.127
What word from Harrenhal?

55
00:05:38.421 --> 00:05:42.634
If Vhagar does not come.
our defenses will not hold.

56
00:05:48.390 --> 00:05:50.225
Do not be disheartened. Daeron.

57
00:05:51.935 --> 00:05:53.603
Your brother will join us soon.

58
00:05:58.608 --> 00:06:01.111
Why seize Tumbleton?

59
00:06:01.194 --> 00:06:04.155
It's no stronghold. It's a market town.

60
00:06:04.239 --> 00:06:07.367
Its lord is meek.
Its walls are poorly defended.

61
00:06:07.450 --> 00:06:09.786
Hightower may as well
paint a rondel on his chest.

62
00:06:09.870 --> 00:06:10.871
Why?

63
00:06:11.955 --> 00:06:14.165
Does he mean to somehow win their support?

64
00:06:16.251 --> 00:06:20.672
He dares me to rain fire down on a seat
that raised my banner.

65
00:06:21.339 --> 00:06:23.633
And the realm would name me
"Maegor Returned."

66
00:06:23.717 --> 00:06:25.552
They'd rise up against me.

67
00:06:25.635 --> 00:06:28.221
And the same gods
who delivered me to the throne

68
00:06:28.305 --> 00:06:29.639
would rightly cast me down.

69
00:06:29.723 --> 00:06:31.516
If I may.

70
00:06:32.433 --> 00:06:36.605
Your Grace. Prince Daemon's river host
marches on King's Landing.

71
00:06:36.688 --> 00:06:38.982
Tumbleton is not much further.

72
00:06:39.065 --> 00:06:41.359
If his men were to go there instead...

73
00:06:41.443 --> 00:06:44.362
Mm. it would not be bloodless.

74
00:06:44.446 --> 00:06:47.490
but it would be far more merciful
than sending dragons.

75
00:06:49.534 --> 00:06:51.119
We march on the town

76
00:06:51.202 --> 00:06:53.622
and root out the Hightowers
house to house.

77
00:06:55.665 --> 00:06:57.375
It's a good scheme.

78
00:06:57.459 --> 00:06:59.085
Send orders to Lord Tully.

79
00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:02.422
Orwyle?

80
00:07:04.007 --> 00:07:07.302
For as long as you remain
loyal and useful...

81
00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:12.390
you may take your place at my council
and retain the title of Grand Maester.

82
00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:18.146
The castle's ravens remain your charge.

83
00:07:18.229 --> 00:07:20.732
but the Lady Mysaria should be
kept informed of the comings and goings.

84
00:07:21.775 --> 00:07:22.776
Ah.

85
00:07:23.735 --> 00:07:26.655
Relics of a dead regime.

86
00:07:29.532 --> 00:07:32.243
It will take the Rivermen weeks
to reach Tumbleton.

87
00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:34.746
Let us send a dragon to keep vigil.

88
00:07:34.829 --> 00:07:37.207
Ormund may have the town under siege.

89
00:07:37.290 --> 00:07:40.251
but he shall not leave
except I remove him.

90
00:07:40.335 --> 00:07:45.048
In the meantime.
we have urgent matters at home.

91
00:07:45.131 --> 00:07:47.550
We have secured some small store of oil

92
00:07:47.634 --> 00:07:49.302
-for the markets. but--
-Where is the Hand?

93
00:07:51.346 --> 00:07:52.764
Gods. this council's thin.

94
00:07:58.728 --> 00:08:00.438
Name a Master of Coin.

95
00:08:01.439 --> 00:08:04.943
The people will soon discover
our lacking resources.

96
00:08:05.026 --> 00:08:07.028
They can blame him.

97
00:08:11.491 --> 00:08:13.994
Investigate Ser Torrhen Manderly.

98
00:08:14.077 --> 00:08:15.829
He's intrigued me.

99
00:08:15.912 --> 00:08:18.790
If he's fit. let the gold be his concern
as well as Daemon's.

100
00:08:20.417 --> 00:08:22.919
Mine shall be Ormund Hightower.

101
00:08:26.589 --> 00:08:28.299
I know him as well as you.

102
00:08:28.383 --> 00:08:30.468
I doubt that.

103
00:08:31.469 --> 00:08:34.222
Viserys warded your son to him.
I've never met the man.

104
00:08:35.597 --> 00:08:39.894
I knew him very little. a long time ago.

105
00:08:39.977 --> 00:08:42.772
After my father took me to court.
I rarely saw Oldtown.

106
00:08:42.856 --> 00:08:44.107
Tell me what you do know.

107
00:08:49.571 --> 00:08:51.948
He sees himself as a scholar.

108
00:08:53.116 --> 00:08:54.909
He studies the histories.

109
00:08:54.993 --> 00:08:58.163
he collects tapestries. writes ballads.

110
00:08:58.246 --> 00:09:00.123
despises the ignorant and uncouth.

111
00:09:01.624 --> 00:09:03.376
When we were young.
Gwayne thought him cruel.

112
00:09:03.460 --> 00:09:05.754
but Gwayne thought that of many.

113
00:09:05.837 --> 00:09:07.088
How is he with Daeron?

114
00:09:09.549 --> 00:09:11.009
Fatherly. I'm told.

115
00:09:11.760 --> 00:09:13.887
Daeron was only a babe
when he took him to ward.

116
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:16.389
What is it?

117
00:09:17.265 --> 00:09:18.767
Oh. look at this.

118
00:09:18.850 --> 00:09:22.020
Did it pain you to have
to send your child away?

119
00:09:26.649 --> 00:09:28.318
It was my choice.

120
00:09:29.360 --> 00:09:30.361
Why?

121
00:09:34.491 --> 00:09:38.745
I bore Viserys three Targaryens.

122
00:09:40.246 --> 00:09:41.956
But with the last. my last...

123
00:09:43.249 --> 00:09:45.168
I wanted him to be a Hightower.

124
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:51.299
In truth. I'm glad I waged that battle.
seeing now what came of our other sons.

125
00:09:51.925 --> 00:09:55.345
Perhaps sending Daeron away
was my truest act of motherhood.

126
00:09:58.306 --> 00:10:01.434
Though I do not know now what fate
that choice has consigned him.

127
00:10:09.526 --> 00:10:11.820
You know I would have spared him.

128
00:10:21.621 --> 00:10:23.957
He has a sensitivity to odors.

129
00:10:25.875 --> 00:10:26.876
Ormund.

130
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:29.879
A very strong one.

131
00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:36.845
My Lord Hand. the queen has requested
your presence at her small council.

132
00:10:36.928 --> 00:10:39.556
I'm her Hand. not her mouth.

133
00:10:39.639 --> 00:10:41.808
Leave the talking to those who relish it.

134
00:10:41.891 --> 00:10:44.769
Shall I return with this message?
That you refuse the queen?

135
00:10:44.853 --> 00:10:47.480
Rather that I serve more effectively.

136
00:10:47.564 --> 00:10:50.150
Her strength lies in dragons now.

137
00:10:50.233 --> 00:10:52.402
She has less need of a man of the sea.

138
00:10:54.654 --> 00:10:57.699
But my son shall attend her in my stead.

139
00:10:57.782 --> 00:10:59.409
You certainly look the part.

140
00:11:00.910 --> 00:11:02.954
I am not a creature of the court.

141
00:11:03.037 --> 00:11:04.747
I don't know what I'm doing.

142
00:11:04.831 --> 00:11:07.167
There is great opportunity for you there.

143
00:11:08.835 --> 00:11:10.837
I cannot give you legitimacy.

144
00:11:10.920 --> 00:11:13.423
but I can give you the chance
to better yourself.

145
00:11:18.469 --> 00:11:22.056
Anger is not something that can
be ended with a blade. my lord.

146
00:11:26.603 --> 00:11:27.854
Move out!

147
00:11:39.199 --> 00:11:40.366
Come on!

148
00:12:36.381 --> 00:12:38.216
My boy.

149
00:12:39.425 --> 00:12:40.718
I'm here.

150
00:12:42.720 --> 00:12:43.888
I'm here.

151
00:12:47.976 --> 00:12:50.103
It's a penny to touch the dragon.

152
00:12:52.021 --> 00:12:54.232
Nothing's free in these woods.

153
00:12:54.816 --> 00:12:57.026
He can sit the saddle for a halfgroat.

154
00:12:57.110 --> 00:12:58.653
Touch will suffice.

155
00:12:58.736 --> 00:13:00.113
Thank you.

156
00:13:05.660 --> 00:13:07.078
We seek shelter.

157
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:08.371
Which way to Rook's Rest?

158
00:13:09.122 --> 00:13:11.165
He's got both hands on him.

159
00:13:11.249 --> 00:13:12.542
That's two touches.

160
00:13:30.977 --> 00:13:32.770
What's wrong with your leg?

161
00:13:37.108 --> 00:13:41.195
You can kill a man of the Faith
for a few pennies. if you wish.

162
00:13:42.739 --> 00:13:45.366
Though I doubt the gods
would look kindly upon it.

163
00:13:45.450 --> 00:13:47.452
You don't look like a septon.

164
00:13:47.535 --> 00:13:48.995
He's alive.

165
00:13:53.415 --> 00:13:56.044
I know it. He's alive. he must be.

166
00:13:56.127 --> 00:13:58.129
-Sunfyre.
-There. there. Gregor.

167
00:13:58.212 --> 00:13:59.672
Wake up. Sunfyre. I'm here.

168
00:13:59.756 --> 00:14:01.883
Let us trouble these
good folk no further. hm?

169
00:14:01.966 --> 00:14:03.968
Wake up. Sunfyre. I'm here.

170
00:14:04.052 --> 00:14:05.345
Simple.

171
00:14:08.639 --> 00:14:10.433
What's he saying?

172
00:14:10.516 --> 00:14:12.643
Sunfyre. come back to me.

173
00:14:12.727 --> 00:14:14.854
Wake up. I'm here.
I know you're in there.

174
00:14:14.937 --> 00:14:17.648
We must tarry no longer.
The danger is great.

175
00:14:17.732 --> 00:14:22.362
I am very sorry.
but you must accept what is before you.

176
00:14:25.114 --> 00:14:26.324
Wake up.

177
00:14:26.407 --> 00:14:29.077
You wanted to see him. you've seen him.

178
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:32.205
-He's dead.
-No.

179
00:14:32.997 --> 00:14:34.957
Will you stay and rot with him?

180
00:14:36.584 --> 00:14:39.379
Will you get up and live?

181
00:15:55.663 --> 00:15:57.165
Are you lost?

182
00:16:02.086 --> 00:16:03.713
Where is the castellan?

183
00:16:06.424 --> 00:16:07.758
Slain.

184
00:16:08.593 --> 00:16:09.969
He who succeeds him then.

185
00:16:11.929 --> 00:16:13.431
Slain.

186
00:16:13.514 --> 00:16:15.475
And the one who succeeds him as well.

187
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:18.352
And who are you?

188
00:16:19.228 --> 00:16:21.397
A steward. of a sort.

189
00:16:22.482 --> 00:16:24.025
It's the best you can do at the moment.

190
00:16:24.108 --> 00:16:25.776
This is the Hand of the King.

191
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.154
We seek the Prince Aemond.

192
00:16:30.072 --> 00:16:32.074
As I'm sure do many.

193
00:16:35.578 --> 00:16:37.830
He was meant to meet us here.

194
00:16:37.914 --> 00:16:39.123
If you know where he is.

195
00:16:39.207 --> 00:16:40.917
I'd advise you to be forthcoming.

196
00:16:45.796 --> 00:16:47.131
He was here.

197
00:16:48.299 --> 00:16:51.469
He seized the castle after
Prince Daemon abandoned it.

198
00:16:51.552 --> 00:16:54.222
but when he learned that
Rhaenyra took King's Landing.

199
00:16:54.305 --> 00:16:57.141
-he and his dragon fled.
-When Rhaenyra took King's Landing?

200
00:17:03.022 --> 00:17:04.315
Oh. my.

201
00:17:05.566 --> 00:17:07.026
Oh. you didn't know.

202
00:17:12.990 --> 00:17:14.909
We've scoured the area. my Lord Hand.

203
00:17:14.992 --> 00:17:17.161
There is sign of a large dragon nest

204
00:17:17.244 --> 00:17:18.538
but it has been abandoned.

205
00:17:19.622 --> 00:17:22.250
Prince Aemond may indeed have fled.

206
00:17:32.843 --> 00:17:34.470
King's Landing has fallen.

207
00:17:34.554 --> 00:17:37.682
Aegon is dead.
our queens are both in chains.

208
00:17:37.765 --> 00:17:42.228
and we are here alone
with a meager army and no dragon.

209
00:17:44.188 --> 00:17:46.023
We have the enemy just where we want them.

210
00:17:48.568 --> 00:17:50.152
Aemond would not desert me.

211
00:17:50.236 --> 00:17:52.905
And yet he's not here. is he?

212
00:17:55.074 --> 00:17:56.784
Let us send a raven to Tumbleton.

213
00:17:57.743 --> 00:17:59.745
Alert my cousin of this news

214
00:17:59.829 --> 00:18:02.331
and our intent
to join our strength to his.

215
00:18:02.415 --> 00:18:05.585
Ormund is a stiff-necked windbag.
but he's neither craven nor stupid.

216
00:18:06.252 --> 00:18:08.629
He will have some canny plot afoot.

217
00:18:11.382 --> 00:18:12.383
No.

218
00:18:18.222 --> 00:18:21.142
The game is played.
Ser Criston. and it is lost.

219
00:18:22.184 --> 00:18:24.061
What possible profit
is there in pursuing it?

220
00:18:28.899 --> 00:18:31.902
You noble ilk conceive this
all a great game. don't you?

221
00:18:31.986 --> 00:18:34.572
To win. to lose. go home to a feather bed.

222
00:18:36.741 --> 00:18:38.993
I was a foot soldier. Did you know that?

223
00:18:39.076 --> 00:18:40.453
Steward's son.

224
00:18:40.536 --> 00:18:43.331
All my father had was at
the pleasure of Lord Dondarrion.

225
00:18:43.414 --> 00:18:45.791
When his favor failed.
all we had melted away.

226
00:18:49.045 --> 00:18:50.880
My father died of sorrow.

227
00:18:51.881 --> 00:18:53.924
There is no home for one like me.

228
00:18:56.552 --> 00:18:58.554
Not while Rhaenyra sits the throne.

229
00:19:01.891 --> 00:19:03.476
Our task is simple.

230
00:19:04.852 --> 00:19:06.604
Keep the river scum
from reaching King's Landing.

231
00:19:06.687 --> 00:19:08.397
Give Ormund time to swell his ranks.

232
00:19:08.481 --> 00:19:10.775
Their army is ten times our size.

233
00:19:10.858 --> 00:19:11.984
Twenty.

234
00:19:12.068 --> 00:19:13.778
But let us attack it...

235
00:19:14.612 --> 00:19:16.614
as the scorpion does the ox.

236
00:19:19.367 --> 00:19:22.870
Let us become wraiths
with fear as our standard.

237
00:19:22.953 --> 00:19:24.413
Strike from the quiet and the darkness.

238
00:19:24.497 --> 00:19:26.540
Our fight will not be clean.
but it will be pure.

239
00:19:28.376 --> 00:19:29.627
We'll be man-to-man.

240
00:19:32.672 --> 00:19:34.423
And it will be free from dragons.

241
00:19:39.720 --> 00:19:42.306
-Ser Edgar!
-We'll delay them at most.

242
00:19:44.600 --> 00:19:46.977
-It will not change their course.
-Perhaps not.

243
00:19:47.061 --> 00:19:49.355
But it is as you said. Ser Gwayne.

244
00:19:49.438 --> 00:19:52.983
We must cling to our honor.
lest we become beasts ourselves.

245
00:20:18.092 --> 00:20:19.510
Who goes there?

246
00:20:19.593 --> 00:20:20.970
Alyn of Hull.

247
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:22.972
I'll see him. Come.

248
00:20:25.015 --> 00:20:26.225
Your Grace.

249
00:20:27.184 --> 00:20:29.979
Lord Corlys has ridden out
by the Dragon Gate

250
00:20:30.062 --> 00:20:32.565
to hunt the Triarchy raiders
that plague our trade.

251
00:20:34.483 --> 00:20:36.694
He has able men who could
lead that campaign.

252
00:20:38.279 --> 00:20:42.116
While his queen struggles
to restore a broken kingdom.

253
00:20:46.036 --> 00:20:47.997
Your Grace. if I may.

254
00:20:49.582 --> 00:20:55.171
My lord father has lost much
and found himself thwarted.

255
00:20:56.130 --> 00:21:00.009
A fight is mayhaps what he needs.

256
00:21:02.470 --> 00:21:03.846
Hm.

257
00:21:06.891 --> 00:21:07.725
Oh.

258
00:21:08.768 --> 00:21:12.813
My father's life's work.
a recreation of the seat of Old Valyria.

259
00:21:14.565 --> 00:21:16.776
A reminder to him. I think. that...

260
00:21:18.861 --> 00:21:20.780
even great dynasties fall.

261
00:21:21.906 --> 00:21:24.241
That the crown should
never rest easy on his head.

262
00:21:26.410 --> 00:21:29.663
There were those who whispered
that my father was weak.

263
00:21:29.747 --> 00:21:30.664
But...

264
00:21:31.624 --> 00:21:34.835
seeing through his eyes.
I can only marvel

265
00:21:34.919 --> 00:21:36.879
at how he kept it
all in balance for so long.

266
00:21:38.422 --> 00:21:44.178
Fathers have a maddening capacity
to at once inspire and incense.

267
00:21:44.929 --> 00:21:46.096
Don't you think?

268
00:21:48.557 --> 00:21:50.351
Gods. they are incessant.

269
00:21:52.228 --> 00:21:54.730
And thanks to Aegon.
all the rat catchers are dead.

270
00:21:56.273 --> 00:21:58.192
On board ship. we kept cats.

271
00:22:02.321 --> 00:22:03.656
Steel yourself.

272
00:22:04.990 --> 00:22:08.160
We must guard our intents whilst I quietly

273
00:22:09.703 --> 00:22:11.997
investigate hiring a ship.

274
00:22:12.081 --> 00:22:14.834
This is Cole's garrison.
They owe allegiance to me.

275
00:22:14.917 --> 00:22:16.544
This is no garrison.

276
00:22:17.586 --> 00:22:20.422
You must presume these men
hold allegiance only to themselves.

277
00:22:27.304 --> 00:22:29.223
We cannot tarry here long.

278
00:23:01.171 --> 00:23:03.924
Good day. friend.
We seek food and shelter.

279
00:23:06.010 --> 00:23:08.971
Like many here gathered.
we are the dispossessed of the war.

280
00:23:09.054 --> 00:23:10.973
You Riverfolk?

281
00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:16.228
I fucking hate Riverfolk.

282
00:23:16.896 --> 00:23:18.522
We hail from Sharp Point.

283
00:23:19.273 --> 00:23:21.025
Prince Aemond burned it to the ground.

284
00:23:22.484 --> 00:23:23.861
W-w-with his d...

285
00:23:27.865 --> 00:23:30.284
-How'd you get out?
-We nearly didn't.

286
00:23:33.245 --> 00:23:35.039
As you can see.

287
00:23:36.749 --> 00:23:38.375
Hm.

288
00:23:46.967 --> 00:23:48.135
Well...

289
00:23:49.178 --> 00:23:51.180
We're too many.

290
00:23:51.263 --> 00:23:52.640
Fuck off.

291
00:23:53.849 --> 00:23:55.392
I have some coin.

292
00:24:10.032 --> 00:24:13.327
You can earn a tent
if you're ready to work.

293
00:24:13.410 --> 00:24:14.703
Have you got a trade?

294
00:24:14.787 --> 00:24:18.832
I have some knowledge of herbs.
and I can read a little.

295
00:24:23.212 --> 00:24:24.713
Maybe you'll be useful.

296
00:24:25.464 --> 00:24:27.174
I have the command around here.

297
00:24:27.257 --> 00:24:30.761
Oh. that much is clear. my lord.

298
00:24:30.844 --> 00:24:32.429
Tangletongue works the latrines.

299
00:24:33.806 --> 00:24:36.350
Collects piss for the tanners.
shit for the farmers.

300
00:24:37.893 --> 00:24:39.353
This one can help him.

301
00:24:39.979 --> 00:24:41.355
Separate buckets.

302
00:24:41.438 --> 00:24:43.315
Mix it up. they won't pay.

303
00:24:44.233 --> 00:24:47.277
I won't touch the fucking latrines--

304
00:24:47.361 --> 00:24:49.321
Just do as they say. Gregor.

305
00:24:49.405 --> 00:24:51.115
-For now. hm?
-I can read just as well as he can.

306
00:24:51.198 --> 00:24:53.492
Tangletongue and Mangleface.

307
00:24:58.122 --> 00:24:59.832
-You'll be good together.
-It's not bad...

308
00:24:59.915 --> 00:25:01.709
-Don't fucking touch me.
-...once you're used to it. brother.

309
00:25:03.419 --> 00:25:04.962
Come on.

310
00:25:07.506 --> 00:25:08.590
Come on.

311
00:25:09.216 --> 00:25:10.759
Fuck off!

312
00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:21.603
I think we'll have
a nice time here tonight.

313
00:25:21.687 --> 00:25:25.107
We'll make merry tonight.
It'll be better than Honeyholt.

314
00:25:36.535 --> 00:25:37.661
Wait.

315
00:25:45.794 --> 00:25:48.172
I need to inspect the goods.

316
00:25:56.722 --> 00:25:57.973
Go and fetch some rosemary.

317
00:26:05.147 --> 00:26:06.690
Come on.

318
00:26:13.155 --> 00:26:15.365
Don't touch her!
Take your hands off of her!

319
00:26:25.375 --> 00:26:26.835
Get them out of here! Get them out!

320
00:26:26.919 --> 00:26:29.088
Get your hands off my brother.
you Hightower--

321
00:26:38.055 --> 00:26:39.807
Ser Hugh Hammer. Your Grace.

322
00:26:41.433 --> 00:26:43.143
Ser Hugh. I assure you.

323
00:26:43.227 --> 00:26:45.896
when there is news of a house.
you will be sent for.

324
00:26:47.523 --> 00:26:50.901
I understand that Ser Ulf
is to be sent to Tumbleton.

325
00:26:50.984 --> 00:26:53.487
-He is.
-If it pleases Your Grace.

326
00:26:53.570 --> 00:26:55.864
I offer to take the watch on Vermithor.

327
00:26:58.033 --> 00:27:00.202
Your wife is at Tumbleton. is she not?

328
00:27:00.285 --> 00:27:01.745
Ser Ulf has no stake in the matter.

329
00:27:01.829 --> 00:27:03.372
Send me. because I do.

330
00:27:04.373 --> 00:27:07.126
I will not tire of watching
when one I love is below.

331
00:27:10.838 --> 00:27:12.172
Take it in turn between you.

332
00:27:12.256 --> 00:27:14.675
Keep watch on the town and on each other.

333
00:27:14.758 --> 00:27:16.301
You may take the first post.

334
00:27:16.385 --> 00:27:18.095
See that Ulf is alerted to the plan.

335
00:27:20.013 --> 00:27:21.390
Your Grace.

336
00:27:29.606 --> 00:27:31.400
Disgusting.

337
00:27:35.445 --> 00:27:37.114
What's it say?

338
00:27:40.492 --> 00:27:42.035
"Queen of Bastards."

339
00:27:43.245 --> 00:27:46.540
Hightower loyalists
trying to fight a war they lost.

340
00:27:53.255 --> 00:27:55.883
So. he has returned.

341
00:27:59.428 --> 00:28:01.221
-Come on!
-Come on.

342
00:28:01.305 --> 00:28:03.265
-Ah! Good evening. ser!
-Hey!

343
00:28:03.348 --> 00:28:06.810
Ulf. the Dragonlord! Hey. hey.

344
00:28:06.894 --> 00:28:08.562
More god than man.

345
00:28:08.645 --> 00:28:11.982
Hey. will you honor your friends
with a round of drinks. my lord?

346
00:28:12.065 --> 00:28:14.151
The price keeps rising. we can't keep up.

347
00:28:14.234 --> 00:28:16.069
-Tell him.
-For everyone.

348
00:28:16.153 --> 00:28:17.696
Hear that?

349
00:28:17.779 --> 00:28:20.449
Drinks for everyone!

350
00:28:25.495 --> 00:28:27.039
-He broke my arm.
-That one broke my nose.

351
00:28:27.122 --> 00:28:28.123
-He attacked my sister.
-You call yourself soldiers.

352
00:28:28.207 --> 00:28:29.208
This is a disgrace.

353
00:28:29.291 --> 00:28:30.751
-The children are terrified.
-What is this?

354
00:28:32.544 --> 00:28:35.964
You said your men were honorable.
This one has sinned.

355
00:28:39.176 --> 00:28:41.261
I was billeted at the smithy. my lord.

356
00:28:41.345 --> 00:28:44.056
But the smith didn't like it.

357
00:28:44.139 --> 00:28:46.558
Mayhaps he resents the imposition.

358
00:28:47.601 --> 00:28:49.728
Or mayhaps he is loyal to Rhaenyra.

359
00:28:50.646 --> 00:28:51.939
But he struck me.

360
00:28:52.022 --> 00:28:55.400
My lord. Now. if it please you.
we bear you no ill will.

361
00:28:55.484 --> 00:28:57.861
But this man went to ravish my sister

362
00:28:57.945 --> 00:29:00.656
and then broke my wife's arm
when she tried to stop him.

363
00:29:00.739 --> 00:29:02.407
She is a weaver.

364
00:29:02.491 --> 00:29:04.368
We need what little she earns.

365
00:29:05.494 --> 00:29:07.746
-Is this true?
-No. my lord.

366
00:29:07.829 --> 00:29:09.373
-Liar!
-Look at this woman's arm.

367
00:29:09.456 --> 00:29:11.375
-She attacked me.
-Is there no safety

368
00:29:11.458 --> 00:29:12.793
-in our houses anymore?
-She called me a cunt!

369
00:29:12.876 --> 00:29:14.503
I will have calm.

370
00:29:18.799 --> 00:29:21.385
-What is your name?
-Garrick. my lord.

371
00:29:21.468 --> 00:29:22.761
of Whitegrove.

372
00:29:22.844 --> 00:29:24.805
Garrick of Whitegrove.

373
00:29:25.973 --> 00:29:27.724
You have violated guest right.

374
00:29:28.558 --> 00:29:32.145
You have debauched yourself
upon a woman and injured another.

375
00:29:32.229 --> 00:29:34.189
Your punishment will fit your crime.

376
00:29:34.273 --> 00:29:35.816
You will be gelded.

377
00:29:35.899 --> 00:29:39.152
And you will have your own arm broken.

378
00:29:39.236 --> 00:29:42.572
You may remain in my service.
but trespass again. and you will hang.

379
00:29:42.656 --> 00:29:45.117
My lord. I have a wife.

380
00:29:45.200 --> 00:29:47.411
Oh! My lord!

381
00:29:47.494 --> 00:29:48.870
-Come on!
-No!

382
00:29:48.954 --> 00:29:51.331
See them home.
Have a maester tend to their wounds.

383
00:29:52.457 --> 00:29:53.667
No!

384
00:29:54.668 --> 00:29:55.919
My lord!

385
00:29:57.337 --> 00:29:58.463
We must keep a firm grip.

386
00:29:59.214 --> 00:30:00.590
Tensions are high.

387
00:30:01.591 --> 00:30:04.636
Lawlessness and disorder
claw at our gates.

388
00:30:04.720 --> 00:30:06.013
Yes. sire.

389
00:30:15.856 --> 00:30:17.274
I wish to see all correspondence

390
00:30:17.357 --> 00:30:20.694
between the Red Keep and Ormund Hightower
since my father's death.

391
00:30:21.486 --> 00:30:22.612
Your Grace.

392
00:30:25.574 --> 00:30:28.118
How much control do the Hightowers

393
00:30:28.201 --> 00:30:29.911
exert over the Faith?

394
00:30:29.995 --> 00:30:34.041
Well. they endowed the building
of the Starry Sept

395
00:30:34.124 --> 00:30:36.168
and Oldtown was their seat for.

396
00:30:36.251 --> 00:30:38.170
well. centuries before the Conquest.

397
00:30:39.212 --> 00:30:41.840
The Seven are as intrinsic
to the Hightower fabric

398
00:30:41.923 --> 00:30:44.968
as. well. dragons are to House Targaryen.

399
00:30:45.052 --> 00:30:46.887
But control. I think not.

400
00:30:46.970 --> 00:30:50.015
The Faith is too proud
to allow such influence.

401
00:30:51.933 --> 00:30:54.561
The High Septon has refused to anoint me.

402
00:30:56.813 --> 00:31:00.108
The Faith clings tightly
to its separate powers.

403
00:31:03.111 --> 00:31:07.407
If I may be so bold to ask Your Grace...

404
00:31:08.283 --> 00:31:09.659
does it matter?

405
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:11.870
Your Grace sits the throne.

406
00:31:11.953 --> 00:31:14.998
Your people have welcomed
you back as a liberator.

407
00:31:15.082 --> 00:31:16.625
Your dragons rule the skies.

408
00:31:16.708 --> 00:31:19.211
Are these not symbols of power enough?

409
00:31:20.712 --> 00:31:23.173
Perhaps I could remove him.

410
00:31:23.256 --> 00:31:27.886
The monarch has ever had some influence
in the naming of the High Septon.

411
00:31:27.969 --> 00:31:30.931
but to remove him altogether
would surely...

412
00:31:31.014 --> 00:31:33.975
incite the Faith.
and therefore the faithful.

413
00:31:36.144 --> 00:31:38.522
Unless you were considering a more...

414
00:31:40.649 --> 00:31:42.234
permanent removal.

415
00:31:44.361 --> 00:31:46.154
I never thought you
so bloodthirsty. Orwyle.

416
00:31:46.238 --> 00:31:48.198
-Ah.
-Rather impressed.

417
00:31:48.281 --> 00:31:49.741
Alas. no.

418
00:31:49.825 --> 00:31:51.827
Bring Ormund's letters
once you have collated them.

419
00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:55.539
There's been no word from
Prince Daemon on his progress?

420
00:31:55.622 --> 00:31:57.374
None as yet. Your Grace.

421
00:32:03.171 --> 00:32:06.216
I had thought never to see you
in the Vale again. Prince Daemon.

422
00:32:07.050 --> 00:32:09.970
What after the tragic death
of your first wife.

423
00:32:11.513 --> 00:32:14.224
And yet I receive raven after raven
from my bannermen

424
00:32:14.307 --> 00:32:17.144
informing me of your progress
throughout my domain.

425
00:32:18.603 --> 00:32:21.106
Time heals even the deepest of wounds.

426
00:32:23.150 --> 00:32:25.986
I am most delighted to return. my lady.

427
00:32:28.363 --> 00:32:31.283
And who could ever fail to be
charmed by your...

428
00:32:31.783 --> 00:32:32.784
warmth.

429
00:32:32.868 --> 00:32:34.578
But I mustn't tarry.

430
00:32:34.661 --> 00:32:37.831
You promised the crown men
in return for a dragon.

431
00:32:37.914 --> 00:32:40.250
Now. you had your dragon.
yet we have no men.

432
00:32:42.210 --> 00:32:44.379
I should send babes.

433
00:32:44.463 --> 00:32:45.922
Prince Joffrey's dragon was years away

434
00:32:46.006 --> 00:32:47.883
from being large enough
to defend the Vale.

435
00:32:47.966 --> 00:32:49.593
and Rhaenyra took even that away.

436
00:32:50.594 --> 00:32:52.345
A less forbearing person

437
00:32:52.429 --> 00:32:54.347
might have seen the crown's offering
as an insult.

438
00:32:54.431 --> 00:32:57.142
-A pledge is a pledge.
-It was my understanding

439
00:32:57.225 --> 00:32:59.269
that the war was won. my prince.

440
00:32:59.352 --> 00:33:02.772
What need does she have of more soldiers?

441
00:33:04.441 --> 00:33:05.567
In truth...

442
00:33:06.860 --> 00:33:09.571
I have not come for men.
I've come for gold.

443
00:33:09.654 --> 00:33:11.656
Huh. so your coffers are empty?

444
00:33:11.740 --> 00:33:13.158
The work of Hightower treachery.

445
00:33:13.241 --> 00:33:16.578
But perhaps a generous offering of coin
would demonstrate your...

446
00:33:17.787 --> 00:33:19.915
fealty to the crown.

447
00:33:19.998 --> 00:33:23.502
Prince Daemon Targaryen.
standing in my high hall.

448
00:33:23.585 --> 00:33:25.795
a beggar with a tin cup.

449
00:33:27.380 --> 00:33:29.216
I never thought I'd live
to see such a sight.

450
00:33:29.299 --> 00:33:32.886
A gift of gold would offer you the benefit
of my speedy departure.

451
00:33:38.391 --> 00:33:39.726
Very well.

452
00:33:46.983 --> 00:33:48.151
Hey!

453
00:33:55.033 --> 00:33:56.284
Hey!

454
00:35:10.358 --> 00:35:11.985
Reveal yourself!

455
00:35:36.760 --> 00:35:38.303
Rhaena.

456
00:35:58.031 --> 00:35:59.949
-Lykiri!
-Daor.

457
00:36:00.033 --> 00:36:01.493
Lykiri.

458
00:36:11.544 --> 00:36:13.755
What have you done to yourself?

459
00:36:19.219 --> 00:36:20.845
How?

460
00:36:23.640 --> 00:36:25.016
I fed him sheep.

461
00:36:28.937 --> 00:36:31.314
Rhaenyra believes this dragon
and his rider are the reason...

462
00:36:33.650 --> 00:36:35.276
Jace is dead.

463
00:36:39.656 --> 00:36:41.866
-I wanted only to help.
-No.

464
00:36:41.950 --> 00:36:44.744
To show her-- to show you
I never intended...

465
00:36:46.454 --> 00:36:47.414
Does she suffer?

466
00:36:51.376 --> 00:36:53.169
Jeyne Arryn knows you're here.

467
00:36:53.253 --> 00:36:55.004
You were meant to accompany
my sons to Pentos.

468
00:36:55.088 --> 00:36:56.673
They are well attended.
They will be safe.

469
00:36:56.756 --> 00:36:58.925
-You swore to be their guardian.
-And do what?

470
00:37:01.219 --> 00:37:03.346
Teach them to be ladies of the realm?

471
00:37:04.514 --> 00:37:06.266
I would be of no use there.

472
00:37:06.349 --> 00:37:08.393
Just as I was of no use here.

473
00:37:11.980 --> 00:37:14.816
If you go now to where
you are meant to be.

474
00:37:14.899 --> 00:37:16.025
Rhaenyra need not know.

475
00:37:16.109 --> 00:37:18.153
We will find a ship.
Leave the dragon behind.

476
00:37:19.070 --> 00:37:20.572
I will not leave him.

477
00:37:20.655 --> 00:37:21.865
He's not like the others. Rhaena.

478
00:37:21.948 --> 00:37:23.575
He is wild. He cannot be trusted.

479
00:37:23.658 --> 00:37:26.035
He is mine. He is a part of me.

480
00:37:27.704 --> 00:37:29.414
I have been alone all my life.

481
00:37:31.332 --> 00:37:35.378
A Targaryen without a dragon.
Disregarded. or...

482
00:37:35.462 --> 00:37:36.629
or worse.

483
00:37:36.713 --> 00:37:38.006
Pitied.

484
00:37:39.632 --> 00:37:42.844
Can you yourself say you ever gave me
more than a passing thought?

485
00:37:42.927 --> 00:37:45.013
Rhaena. the unfortunate.

486
00:37:46.598 --> 00:37:48.892
Rhaena. the least among your children.

487
00:37:52.562 --> 00:37:54.189
Come back with me. then.
to King's Landing.

488
00:37:54.272 --> 00:37:55.899
-No.
-We will...

489
00:37:57.192 --> 00:37:59.444
speak to her together.
We will tell her it was a mistake.

490
00:37:59.527 --> 00:38:03.656
How can I ever stand before her again
after what I have done?

491
00:38:04.699 --> 00:38:06.743
No. I can never return.

492
00:38:06.826 --> 00:38:10.580
I will remain here. alone and in exile.

493
00:38:10.663 --> 00:38:13.124
-That is my penance.
-She will hunt you down.

494
00:38:14.042 --> 00:38:15.335
Is hunting now.

495
00:38:15.418 --> 00:38:18.171
Let them grieve me
and think me lost to sea.

496
00:38:21.299 --> 00:38:23.134
Unless you betray me.

497
00:38:23.218 --> 00:38:25.303
You ask me to deceive her.
That is betrayal.

498
00:38:25.386 --> 00:38:29.015
I have asked you nothing.
Father. in all my life.

499
00:38:31.184 --> 00:38:32.852
I ask this one thing of you now.

500
00:38:32.936 --> 00:38:34.604
Rhaena. Rhaena.

501
00:38:34.687 --> 00:38:35.897
Rhaena!

502
00:38:37.982 --> 00:38:38.983
Rhaena!

503
00:38:56.459 --> 00:38:57.418
Shh!

504
00:39:40.837 --> 00:39:43.673
A raven just arrived
from Harrenhal. my lord.

505
00:39:43.756 --> 00:39:45.800
It bears the Hightower seal.

506
00:40:10.950 --> 00:40:11.951
Get out.

507
00:40:12.785 --> 00:40:14.412
My prince?

508
00:40:14.495 --> 00:40:16.331
Out. Now.

509
00:40:29.552 --> 00:40:31.888
Useless craven coward!

510
00:40:31.971 --> 00:40:33.431
Cunt!

511
00:40:36.601 --> 00:40:38.853
Cunt! Cunt!

512
00:40:38.937 --> 00:40:40.813
Cunt!

513
00:41:09.467 --> 00:41:11.719
Your Uncle Gwayne has sent word.

514
00:41:13.846 --> 00:41:18.101
It seems your brother Aemond
will not be joining us after all.

515
00:41:21.396 --> 00:41:22.313
Is...

516
00:41:23.564 --> 00:41:25.400
Gwayne coming to Tumbleton?

517
00:41:28.194 --> 00:41:30.113
We must alter our scheme.

518
00:41:34.617 --> 00:41:37.078
Ser Otto wrote diligently to Ormund.

519
00:41:37.912 --> 00:41:39.497
Naught was returned.

520
00:41:39.580 --> 00:41:42.000
Are you sure there's been no error?

521
00:41:42.083 --> 00:41:43.084
Nothing?

522
00:41:45.795 --> 00:41:47.296
What am I to make of this?

523
00:41:48.673 --> 00:41:51.509
I suppose only that Lord Ormund

524
00:41:51.592 --> 00:41:54.971
ruled Oldtown as a kingdom unto itself.

525
00:42:14.824 --> 00:42:18.077
Ser Ulf White is still without.
Your Grace.

526
00:42:18.161 --> 00:42:19.287
Oh. uh...

527
00:42:20.538 --> 00:42:21.539
Come.

528
00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:25.084
Your Grace.

529
00:42:26.669 --> 00:42:32.383
I'm honored to be in your service
and to have sworn my life to your cause.

530
00:42:32.467 --> 00:42:33.551
Yes. I'm sure.

531
00:42:34.552 --> 00:42:37.555
-What is it. then?
-Oh. I wondered

532
00:42:37.638 --> 00:42:41.017
whether. as Your Grace's humble servant.

533
00:42:41.100 --> 00:42:44.562
I might petition
for your favor-- er. favors.

534
00:42:45.354 --> 00:42:46.731
Speak them.

535
00:42:46.814 --> 00:42:50.026
For a man named Mujja.

536
00:42:50.109 --> 00:42:54.113
a smallholding outside Rosby

537
00:42:54.197 --> 00:42:56.657
and exemption from taxes.
thanking Your Grace.

538
00:42:56.741 --> 00:42:59.035
And for a fellow named Cley.

539
00:42:59.118 --> 00:43:02.580
a pardon for various small crimes.

540
00:43:02.663 --> 00:43:04.582
We don't have to go into that.
and passage to Lys--

541
00:43:04.665 --> 00:43:06.250
These favors are not in your name.

542
00:43:06.334 --> 00:43:08.169
No. no. Your Grace.

543
00:43:10.004 --> 00:43:11.464
They're for allies...

544
00:43:12.799 --> 00:43:14.759
from a tavern I frequented.

545
00:43:14.842 --> 00:43:17.345
-frequented previously.
-A tavern.

546
00:43:19.597 --> 00:43:23.684
And if an agent of the Hightowers

547
00:43:23.768 --> 00:43:25.978
knifes you in your belly
as you fill it with ale?

548
00:43:26.062 --> 00:43:28.606
No. it's not that sort of place.
Besides...

549
00:43:31.025 --> 00:43:33.945
-It's my belly.
-Oh. but it's not.

550
00:43:34.028 --> 00:43:37.240
No. you belong now to the crown.

551
00:43:37.323 --> 00:43:39.992
Should something befall you.
or your belly.

552
00:43:40.076 --> 00:43:43.913
I suffer the loss of a dragon
and the unity of the realm is threatened.

553
00:43:43.996 --> 00:43:47.166
No. you shall frequent taverns no longer.

554
00:43:47.250 --> 00:43:48.709
What?

555
00:43:48.793 --> 00:43:50.962
Well. I'm afraid
you'll have to find your--

556
00:43:51.045 --> 00:43:53.339
your beer within the walls
of the Red Keep.

557
00:43:53.422 --> 00:43:55.216
where you will remain...

558
00:43:56.175 --> 00:43:58.136
except when you are escorted
to the Dragonpit

559
00:43:58.219 --> 00:43:59.512
for duty at Tumbleton.

560
00:44:00.847 --> 00:44:02.890
If that is all. you may go.

561
00:44:12.859 --> 00:44:14.152
They protest you.

562
00:44:15.319 --> 00:44:18.281
You know. out there in the city.

563
00:44:19.282 --> 00:44:22.201
I've seen vile words painted on walls.

564
00:44:23.995 --> 00:44:25.163
They say...

565
00:44:26.789 --> 00:44:28.207
"Queen of Bastards."

566
00:44:31.919 --> 00:44:36.799
The work. I am sure.
of some of your misguided subjects

567
00:44:36.883 --> 00:44:40.052
who mistakenly believe
their queen to be unkind.

568
00:44:44.932 --> 00:44:46.225
Your Grace.

569
00:45:04.869 --> 00:45:06.913
Can you send word to Ser Luthor?

570
00:45:06.996 --> 00:45:10.374
Have his gold cloaks
look for any seditious markings

571
00:45:10.458 --> 00:45:12.376
on the streets of the city. remove them...

572
00:45:13.711 --> 00:45:15.171
and find those responsible.

573
00:45:16.005 --> 00:45:17.256
And bring them to you. Your Grace?

574
00:45:17.340 --> 00:45:19.926
Just make it cease. please.

575
00:45:40.905 --> 00:45:43.908
There's a Braavosi cog sailing
from Duskendale in a few days.

576
00:45:44.825 --> 00:45:47.161
-I think I can find us fresh horses.
-I'm the fucking king.

577
00:45:47.245 --> 00:45:48.996
If they knew I walked among them.

578
00:45:49.914 --> 00:45:52.792
Even were you to be believed.
Rhaenyra sits the throne.

579
00:45:52.875 --> 00:45:54.543
And you have no dragon.

580
00:45:54.627 --> 00:45:57.004
She did us a favor by declaring you dead.

581
00:45:59.507 --> 00:46:00.549
I'm dead?

582
00:46:00.633 --> 00:46:02.134
Slain by your brother Aemond.

583
00:46:03.427 --> 00:46:05.137
Is that what they say?

584
00:46:05.221 --> 00:46:06.764
Mm.

585
00:46:06.847 --> 00:46:07.932
I'll fucking kill him.

586
00:46:08.015 --> 00:46:10.017
-I'll fucking kill her. the s--
-In time.

587
00:46:12.311 --> 00:46:14.772
There's much to be learned
from the chatter in this camp.

588
00:46:14.855 --> 00:46:18.526
Anonymity is a boon for us.

589
00:46:19.360 --> 00:46:23.739
It will ensure that your
eventual resurrection...

590
00:46:26.200 --> 00:46:28.244
becomes the stuff of song and legend.

591
00:46:32.164 --> 00:46:33.541
Have something to eat.

592
00:46:42.341 --> 00:46:43.801
None left for us.

593
00:46:43.884 --> 00:46:45.303
Happens sometimes. but...

594
00:46:46.220 --> 00:46:48.806
We'll get some tomorrow.

595
00:46:49.640 --> 00:46:51.017
Tomorrow?

596
00:46:54.103 --> 00:46:56.188
I'll not stand for this.

597
00:46:57.189 --> 00:46:58.232
Outrage!

598
00:46:59.358 --> 00:47:01.652
Is this how you rule? Running out of food?

599
00:47:04.405 --> 00:47:05.990
Answer me!

600
00:47:07.074 --> 00:47:09.785
Sit down before I make you.

601
00:47:09.869 --> 00:47:11.162
Who do you think you're talking to?

602
00:47:11.245 --> 00:47:12.955
I'll have your fucking tongue.
you insolent ape.

603
00:47:13.956 --> 00:47:15.249
-Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa.
-Please.

604
00:47:15.333 --> 00:47:19.045
And I'll gut you like a fish. cunt.

605
00:47:19.128 --> 00:47:20.755
Let's...

606
00:47:20.838 --> 00:47:22.048
let's not be hasty.

607
00:47:26.260 --> 00:47:28.012
On your knees.

608
00:47:28.095 --> 00:47:29.388
if you want to live.

609
00:47:54.205 --> 00:47:55.748
Kiss my feet.

610
00:47:57.958 --> 00:48:00.294
-I take it back.
-Or die.

611
00:48:00.378 --> 00:48:01.545
I don't care which.

612
00:48:03.964 --> 00:48:05.591
But you will call me...

613
00:48:06.425 --> 00:48:08.677
-"my lord."
-Janos.

614
00:48:08.761 --> 00:48:10.179
You as well?

615
00:48:37.123 --> 00:48:39.166
The inquisitions were thorough.

616
00:48:39.250 --> 00:48:41.377
We should be assured
that wherever they might be.

617
00:48:41.460 --> 00:48:44.922
the crown's holdings are no longer in...

618
00:48:45.005 --> 00:48:46.132
I bring justice.

619
00:48:50.845 --> 00:48:52.388
I bring vengeance.

620
00:48:53.973 --> 00:48:55.307
I also bring gold.

621
00:48:57.685 --> 00:49:00.062
-What is this?
-The one who rode Sheepstealer.

622
00:49:01.105 --> 00:49:05.443
Along with 10.000 golden dragons
from Lady Jeyne Arryn.

623
00:49:07.695 --> 00:49:09.572
Anything from her bannermen in the Vale?

624
00:49:10.781 --> 00:49:13.200
We still await some response
from the great houses.

625
00:49:13.284 --> 00:49:16.078
And the Iron Bank has not
answered our request for a loan.

626
00:49:16.162 --> 00:49:18.122
Would you please explain who that is?

627
00:49:18.205 --> 00:49:21.792
Ser Torrhen Manderly. my prince.
the new Master of Coin.

628
00:49:21.876 --> 00:49:24.086
What little there is to be a master of.

629
00:49:24.170 --> 00:49:26.714
Well. I'll wager you think you're clever.
don't you. Manderly?

630
00:49:26.797 --> 00:49:28.048
-Well...
-You should know

631
00:49:28.132 --> 00:49:29.592
I'm the clever one around here.

632
00:49:31.719 --> 00:49:33.721
-Say no more.
-What small quantity

633
00:49:33.804 --> 00:49:37.224
of gold Daemon has found
must go to ease the deprivations

634
00:49:37.308 --> 00:49:39.226
-of the smallfolk.
-The City Watch is stretched far too thin.

635
00:49:39.310 --> 00:49:40.644
Our soldiers need to be paid

636
00:49:40.728 --> 00:49:43.272
and more recruited besides.
else there will be bedlam.

637
00:49:43.355 --> 00:49:44.648
-Your Grace--
-Bedlam is assured

638
00:49:44.732 --> 00:49:46.275
if the people feel the crown
ignores their anger.

639
00:49:46.358 --> 00:49:48.611
Has anyone considered a tax?

640
00:49:48.694 --> 00:49:50.279
Clear the room.

641
00:50:07.213 --> 00:50:08.380
What is this?

642
00:50:10.216 --> 00:50:11.425
The queen's justice.

643
00:50:11.509 --> 00:50:12.843
Who is he?

644
00:50:13.886 --> 00:50:16.180
And how did he come
to claim a wild dragon?

645
00:50:16.263 --> 00:50:18.599
Was he alone. or is--

646
00:50:18.682 --> 00:50:21.143
is he allied to Aemond or to Ormund?

647
00:50:21.227 --> 00:50:24.480
I desired the very same answers.
but a dragon is not a precise instrument.

648
00:50:25.564 --> 00:50:27.149
What of Sheepstealer?

649
00:50:27.233 --> 00:50:29.318
Fled. Riderless.

650
00:50:29.401 --> 00:50:31.237
It is an act of madness
to claim a wild dragon.

651
00:50:31.320 --> 00:50:32.863
We are not like to see it again.

652
00:50:39.620 --> 00:50:42.831
I wanted to see him.

653
00:50:46.961 --> 00:50:51.048
I wanted to look on the one
who killed my son.

654
00:50:55.344 --> 00:50:56.929
To punish him yourself?

655
00:50:59.515 --> 00:51:01.642
But do you think
that would end your grief?

656
00:51:02.685 --> 00:51:04.270
I have served your interest.

657
00:51:15.656 --> 00:51:19.076
The gold you brought will
provide alms for the smallfolk.

658
00:51:20.286 --> 00:51:23.205
The City Watch trusts you.
You will entreat them to be patient.

659
00:51:24.540 --> 00:51:26.417
The crown will honor its debt...

660
00:51:27.543 --> 00:51:28.877
a little longer.

661
00:51:35.217 --> 00:51:36.385
I suppose...

662
00:51:37.720 --> 00:51:39.388
I should thank you.

663
00:51:48.606 --> 00:51:52.276
When what you've wrought
comes falling down about her ears.

664
00:51:52.359 --> 00:51:54.945
she'll return to her senses.

665
00:51:55.779 --> 00:51:57.323
Whose head is that?

666
00:52:37.112 --> 00:52:40.366
I have dispatched good men
to see your father's remains

667
00:52:40.449 --> 00:52:41.992
delivered to Oldtown.

668
00:52:50.376 --> 00:52:51.835
Viserys would have wished it.

669
00:52:54.672 --> 00:52:55.798
Thank you.

670
00:53:17.820 --> 00:53:19.071
Here.

671
00:53:31.834 --> 00:53:33.252
Helaena.

672
00:53:39.633 --> 00:53:40.801
Clear the streets.

673
00:53:40.884 --> 00:53:42.302
Clear the streets!

674
00:53:42.386 --> 00:53:44.722
Observe the curfew!

675
00:53:47.808 --> 00:53:49.309
All indoors!

676
00:53:51.145 --> 00:53:52.646
Clear the street!

677
00:53:55.190 --> 00:53:57.818
Stay home or hang!

678
00:53:57.901 --> 00:53:59.737
Dragon!

679
00:54:00.237 --> 00:54:01.238
Dragon!

680
00:54:26.889 --> 00:54:29.892
Open your doors by order of the queen.

681
00:54:29.975 --> 00:54:32.186
Here! Here!

682
00:54:33.395 --> 00:54:34.730
-With me.
-Up here.

683
00:54:34.813 --> 00:54:36.815
Get them out of their home!

684
00:54:36.899 --> 00:54:38.066
Who did this?

685
00:54:39.193 --> 00:54:41.069
Which traitor stained these walls?

686
00:54:41.153 --> 00:54:42.321
Find the hand that stained these walls.

687
00:54:42.404 --> 00:54:44.281
Scrub. Scrub!

688
00:54:46.867 --> 00:54:47.993
Bring them out!

689
00:55:09.306 --> 00:55:11.683
-Has he confessed?
-Not yet.

690
00:55:11.767 --> 00:55:14.144
I haven't done anything. Please.

691
00:55:15.604 --> 00:55:16.647
Please.

692
00:55:17.898 --> 00:55:20.275
Patience. my girl.

693
00:55:21.193 --> 00:55:23.445
It won't be long before we can fly again.

694
00:55:27.241 --> 00:55:29.618
I have warned you
against indulging in affection

695
00:55:29.701 --> 00:55:31.078
for that beast.

696
00:55:33.455 --> 00:55:34.706
Lykiri.

697
00:55:39.920 --> 00:55:41.046
I know.

698
00:55:51.265 --> 00:55:52.724
You are a good boy.

699
00:55:54.393 --> 00:55:57.062
You speak kindly and you say your prayers.

700
00:55:58.230 --> 00:55:59.982
I have raised you
in the light of the Seven.

701
00:56:00.065 --> 00:56:01.900
and the Father smiles upon you.

702
00:56:03.902 --> 00:56:05.946
But there is a taint in your blood.

703
00:56:07.489 --> 00:56:10.200
The Targaryens are a savage race.

704
00:56:10.284 --> 00:56:12.494
poor in intellect. but rich in cunning.

705
00:56:14.246 --> 00:56:17.082
With dark spells.
they created abominations

706
00:56:17.165 --> 00:56:19.001
to subdue what was rightly ours.

707
00:56:22.921 --> 00:56:24.590
We are the superior men.

708
00:56:25.674 --> 00:56:27.926
But against that...

709
00:56:29.761 --> 00:56:31.138
we could not stand.

710
00:56:39.730 --> 00:56:42.357
The gods have put you
to divine purpose. my boy.

711
00:56:43.442 --> 00:56:45.485
What purpose. sire?

712
00:56:46.862 --> 00:56:50.574
The brutes raise a woman
to the Iron Throne.

713
00:56:51.408 --> 00:56:52.534
A desecration!

714
00:56:52.618 --> 00:56:55.287
Where is reason? Where is propriety?

715
00:56:56.330 --> 00:56:58.498
It was a blessing that you
came to ward in Oldtown.

716
00:56:59.541 --> 00:57:01.960
Your brothers are lost. but you...

717
00:57:02.961 --> 00:57:05.005
remain a Hightower.

718
00:57:05.088 --> 00:57:07.382
raised in the shadow of the Citadel.

719
00:57:07.466 --> 00:57:09.927
in the light of the Starry Sept.

720
00:57:14.932 --> 00:57:15.933
Now...

721
00:57:17.100 --> 00:57:18.727
you must be king.

722
00:57:23.857 --> 00:57:26.109
You would not wish. surely.

723
00:57:26.193 --> 00:57:28.612
for me to turn cloak against my brothers.

724
00:57:28.695 --> 00:57:30.948
You will restore our ancient order.

725
00:57:31.031 --> 00:57:33.992
Victory will be ours.
It is the will of the gods.

726
00:57:36.244 --> 00:57:37.788
I thought you let him go.

727
00:57:38.705 --> 00:57:42.542
A righteous king must demonstrate
he upholds many virtues.

728
00:57:42.626 --> 00:57:44.294
Honor. wisdom.

729
00:57:45.087 --> 00:57:46.046
Justice.

730
00:57:46.129 --> 00:57:48.340
He only acted when our man
attacked a woman.

731
00:57:48.423 --> 00:57:50.133
He laid hands on a Hightower.

732
00:57:50.217 --> 00:57:53.428
That soldier is an extension of you.
of the crown.

733
00:57:53.512 --> 00:57:54.972
Justice must be done.

734
00:57:55.055 --> 00:57:57.224
Is not mercy a kingly virtue?

735
00:57:57.307 --> 00:57:59.559
That sounds like something
your father would say.

736
00:58:04.147 --> 00:58:05.190
I'm sorry.

737
00:58:27.212 --> 00:58:30.132
I have risked much
and more to raise you up.

738
00:58:31.967 --> 00:58:34.011
Surely. you do not wish to disappoint me.

739
00:58:50.944 --> 00:58:52.070
My lord.

740
00:58:52.738 --> 00:58:55.240
My lord. please. Please.

741
00:58:55.323 --> 00:58:57.784
No. please. I beg you.

742
00:58:57.868 --> 00:58:59.244
My lord.

743
00:59:00.954 --> 00:59:02.956
Please. I beg you.

744
00:59:04.875 --> 00:59:06.960
I have a family. my lord.

745
00:59:07.044 --> 00:59:08.754
I have a family. Please.

746
00:59:10.172 --> 00:59:11.923
Please. please.

747
01:00:06.812 --> 01:00:08.271
And now we begin.

747
